<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-27T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-27T14:00:00-05:00" n="370" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/374: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reber</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-27T14:00:00-05:00">December 27, 1930—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>120. Your 181, December 24, 2 p.m. In my view, the Liberian note therein
                            quoted changes in no way the Department’s position (see my No. 119,
                            December 20, 3 p.m., and previous). Do not make an acknowledgment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>